# 13. System State Terms

## TERM-031 — Empty State

**Canonical Term:** Empty State

**Korean Meaning:** 표시할 데이터가 존재하지 않는 상태

**Definition:**

A UI state in which a component or section has no applicable data to display.

Empty State behavior may include:

- Showing guidance
- Showing a placeholder
- Remaining hidden

The correct behavior must be defined by the relevant specification.

**Core Rules:**

- Empty panels must not be shown merely to fill UI space.
- Conditional ATA sections may remain hidden when no relevant data exists.
- Empty State behavior must not be left to arbitrary implementation preference.

