# 15. Critical Distinctions

The following distinctions are mandatory across ATA.

## 15.1 Workspace vs Translation Workspace

```text
Workspace
= A translation work unit and its associated state.

Translation Workspace
= The main UI environment where the user works on a Workspace.
```

These terms are not interchangeable.

---

## 15.2 Workspace vs Workspace History

```text
Workspace
= Current or active translation work unit.

Workspace History
= Stored record of previous Workspace activity.
```

History is not automatically Knowledge.

---

## 15.3 AI Recommendation vs User-edited Translation

```text
AI Recommendation
= AI-generated proposed translation.

User-edited Translation
= Translation content explicitly modified by the user.
```

Neither automatically becomes Knowledge.

---

## 15.4 Final Translation vs Knowledge

```text
Final Translation
= Translation considered complete for the current task.

Knowledge
= Approved reusable translation knowledge for future work.
```

A completed translation does not automatically become Knowledge.

---

## 15.5 Knowledge vs Asset

```text
Knowledge
= Trusted reusable translation knowledge as a conceptual state.

Asset
= A structured reusable translation resource represented and managed by ATA.
```

Their detailed relationship must follow F003 and related lifecycle specifications.

---

## 15.6 Asset Recommendation vs History Recommendation

```text
Assets Recommendation
= Surfaces relevant structured reusable translation resources.

History Recommendation
= Surfaces relevant previous translation work.
```

Previous work is not automatically trusted Knowledge.

---

## 15.7 Review vs Knowledge Approval

```text
Review
= A structured examination stage.

Knowledge Approval
= A lifecycle transition into approved reusable Knowledge.
```

Completing Review does not automatically equal Knowledge approval unless explicitly defined.

---

## 15.8 User Flow vs Workspace Flow

```text
User Flow
= The sequence of actions and responses for accomplishing a specific task.

Workspace Flow
= The lifecycle progression of the overall translation work unit.
```

---

## 15.9 OCR Result vs Translation Result

```text
OCR Result
= Text extracted from an image.

Translation Result
= Translated content produced during translation work.
```

OCR is an input mechanism, not translation.

---

# 16. Prohibited Terminology Assumptions

The following assumptions are prohibited unless explicitly approved by the applicable specification.

```text
AI Recommendation = Final Translation
AI Recommendation = Knowledge
User Edit = Knowledge
Final Translation = Knowledge
Workspace History = Knowledge
Workspace History = Asset
Review Completion = Knowledge Approval
OCR Result = Translation Result
Workspace = Translation Workspace
User Flow = Workspace Flow
```

AI systems, developers, and reviewers must preserve these distinctions.

